	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The period-93 mode has the interesting additional property that it randomly contains a very loud 31st harmonic. There's no way for the CPU to detect whether it's in this mode (short of modifying the NES), so it's hard to use intentionally.<br /><br />Previous things I've said:<br /><a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=132677#p132677" class="postlink">3d graph of first 3 harmonics being random</a><br /><a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=172797#p172797" class="postlink">A cold boot can get a very specific waveform from the period-93 mode that's musically useful</a><br /><br />That said, the Ã—31 harmonic does mean that the very low rates actually become useful in tonal noise mode; the slowest rate there does repeat at 5Hz but it also has a conspicuously audible tone at 147Hz.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


