		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It doesn't help that the frequencies on an NTSC deck (in period 93 mode) are ~45cents out of tune with A440</div><br />Wait, to me that sounds helpful?<br /><br />Like the DPCM frequencies are all consistently out of tune by a factor of 17/16 because of that off-by-one error in its loop implementation. I shifted the tuning tables in that NSF to compensate.<br /><br />If the noise frequencies are a fairly consistent deviation from A440 then that in itself is helpful, because it can be compensated by tuning to A440 + 45 cents instead of A440.

		

